definition: to receive/to accept/to collect/to put away/to restrain/to stop/in care of (used on address line after name)

sentences.english: An air transport document must indicate that the goods have been accepted for carriage.

sentences.english: If the fax transmission, Please inform us immediately.

sentences.english: Application will only be processed after receipt of full payment for entry fee.
sentences.chinese: 所有报名表格以收妥参加费用后才作处理。

sentences.english: As space is limited, booking with Cheque is on a first-come, first-served basis.
sentences.chinese: 由于座位有限，以收妥支票先订先得形式进行。
